{"insight":"No Vision Outgrows Correction","publicTitle":"Keep What Can Correct You","plainSummary":"A deep experience deserves trust only when truth, care, and real change can still correct it.","atAGlance":"Powerful experiences can make a person hard to reach. Trust grows when a person still answers to truth, care, duty, and visible change. A path may be set down after it helps, but correction must remain. When nothing can challenge the result, the result is not ready to guide a life.","keyPoints":["Meaning ripens when humility stays stronger than certainty.","Closed certainty can turn help into control or isolation.","Test whether trusted people and real consequences can still change the conclusion."],"match":["keep what can correct you"],"tags":["practice","humility","discernment","safety"]}
